Import process begins by pulling data from WormBase (see util/import/wormbase/README)
followed by merging CGC data.

./merge_cgc_data.pl --dir $IMPORT_DIR

--


Scripts and related files for importing data from the old FoxPro database.

    foxpro_parser.pl
        A utility that parses FoxPro formatted dumps of the legacy CGC
        database and produces tab-delimited files that can be imported into
        the new relational database.

    import.pl
        Loads a set of expected files and populates the relational CGC
        database. The script operates on an input directory that contains
        converted FoxPro dumps and other custom data. Since data in individual
        tables in the new schema potentially draws from multiple import files,
        the files are read in together. The script uses the DBIx::Schema model
        framework to interact (i.e., insert) the data into the database.

    merge_cgc_data.pl
        Merge (and add, when appropriate) CGC data into a database prepopulated
	with data from WormBase.  Logs merged data to logs/import_logs/CLASS-cgc-merged.log
	./util/import/import.pl --verbose 2 --dir $IMPORT_DIR


Creating and populating the CGC Database
========================================
Here's a very terse outline of commands to create and populate the database based on the legacy dumps:

	# Variables
	CGC_DB=cgc
	IMPORT_DIR=/usr/local/cgc/website/production/data/foxpro_dumps/TSV

	# Create database
	mysqladmin create $CGC_DB

	# Initialize schema
	mysql $CGC_DB < schema/cgc.sql

	# Import data from legacy dumps
	./util/import/import.pl --verbose 2 --dir $IMPORT_DIR
	
